# PA-GFP F153A Cavity Engineering Script
# Author: Shen Khaw
# Project: Computational Prediction of Steric Cavities in PA-GFP

# 1. Initialize and Load Structure
reinitialize
# Added ', pagfp' so the rest of the script knows what object to look at!
load T203H_baseline.pdb, pagfp

# 2. Basic Visualization Setup
hide everything
show cartoon, pagfp
select chromo, resi 65-67
show sticks, chromo
color green, chromo

# --- Show the T203H Baseline Residue ---
select t203h, resi 203
show sticks, t203h
color magenta, t203h

# 3. Establish Baseline (T203H)
# Measuring directly between your two selections!
distance baseline_dist, t203h, chromo
# If gives multiple numbers, undo and use measurement wizard from closest amino acids
# Expected result: ~3.3 Å

# 4. Engineer Novel F153A Mutation
wizard mutagenesis
mutagenesis 153, ALA
# (Note: In the GUI, select the best rotamer to minimize clashes, then apply)
apply
wizard 0

# 5. Measure Mutant Distance to Chromophore
# Measuring the new residue 153 to the chromophore
distance mutant_dist, resi 153, chromo
# Expected result: ~13.3 Å (Expanded cavity)

# 6. Visualize the Cavity and Steric Environment
select f153a, resi 153
show sticks, f153a
color yellow, f153a

# 7. Save the Final Mutated Structure
save F153A_PA-GFP_Mutant.pdb, pagfp

# 8. Render a high-quality image for the paper
ray 1200, 1200
png F153A_Cavity_Visualization.png
